Description: Anthropoid wooden inner-coffin of Djedmontuiufankh; painted decoration on plastered linen.
Curator's comments: PM I Part 2: p.829 Taylor, in Strudwick and Taylor (eds): The Theban Necropolis (2003). P.115 [pl.65-66, 68]
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 2008, 3 Mar-20 Jul, Cankarjev Dom, Slovenia, Pharaonic Renaissance. 2008, 4 Aug-9 Nov. Budapest, Museum of Fine Arts, Renaissance in Pharaonic Egypt.
